narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a lot about career options, resolving conflict and many other topics.
Some of the lectures included interesting discussions and introduced us to topics graduate students should be aware of.

I thought the sessions about jobs/grants and record-keeping were probably the most useful, but this was a good survey of several topics relevant to our field that don't necessarily get covered for us in any other format.
knowledge on important things about doing research in the U.S. such as patent, grants and fellowship, confidentiality, etc,.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I can not think of any ways the course can be improved
Strength: - Diverse set of topics Weakness: - Class timing (Thursday late afternoon) - Condensed material in one hour; we did not have enough time for discussion in several sessions
Broad variety of topics kept it interesting. For the most part, there was a lot of student participation, which also kept it more engaging than just a straight-up lecture would. No complaints.
Better to be more related to our studies and experiments.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Good course to know some research ethics
